<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2014-01-16</DATELINE><TITLE>Successful management of Panton-Valentine leukocidine-positive necrotising pneumonia and A/H1N1(2009) influenzavirus coinfection in adult</TITLE><BODY>This paper presents a case of community-acquired necrotising pneumonia due to Panton-Valentine leukocidine-positive methicillin-susceptible Staphylococcus aureus and A/H1N1(2009) influenzavirus co-infection in a 26-year-old woman. Despite the presence of pejorative prognostic factors, the clinical course of the patient was favourable.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>